text.tspan: Q with any pair of delimiters can be used to quote strings verbatim without interpolation
or escaping. Nonetheless, its behavior can be changed through the used of adverbs:
Neither () nor '' can be used as regular delimiters
with Q. To use them, a space must separate them
Strings are usually represented using some form of quoting construct. The most minimalistic
is Q, which can be used with the shortcut 「...」 or via Q inmediately followed by almost any
pair of delimiters surrounding the text.
